<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-4893] Don&apos;t throw internal exceptions over JMX</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-4893</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Similarly to how we don&apos;t return internal objects over JMX we shouldn&apos;t throw internal exceptions over jmx as well.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The one example I encountered was throwing ConfigurationException for the move() command. We should check the rest of our jmx as well.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12614410">CASSANDRA-4893</key>
            <summary>Don&apos;t throw internal exceptions over JMX</summary>
